## Instructions

1. List the contents of `{{ ansible_path }}` to understand the role structure
2. Read ALL task files under `{{ ansible_path }}/tasks/`
3. Read `{{ ansible_path }}/defaults/main.yml` and `{{ ansible_path }}/vars/main.yml` if they exist
4. Read `{{ ansible_path }}/handlers/main.yml` if it exists
5. For each task file, check for:
   - Missing prerequisites (users, groups, directories referenced but never created)
   - Missing package dependencies (config files for packages not installed in the role)
   - Idempotency failures (commands without creates/removes guards)
   - Ordering issues (config before package install, service start before config)
6. Fix each issue you find by rewriting the affected file with minimal changes
7. Produce a review summary report
